        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top'
 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>Ulaa</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'> <BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote> <BR>YES, this was exactly what I was going to say. We need MUCH better dots than Pyre. MUCH MUCH better dots. <BR>Wizards best DD is doing around 1200 dmg, bane spells not included. With a crit they hit for above 3k. They do this damage in 7 seconds.</P><P>Pyre cannot be stacked, cannot crit, can do nothing but do 2k damage in 54 seconds. So casting time included, every minute you can do 2k damage. That is 40 dps..... if you load every single dot on the mob, you can reach about 90 dps or even lower. And you CANNOT load every single dot, because the aggro will kill you. So we are a damage dealing class and do not even reach 90 dps? Even warriors reach 80 dps and guess what, they have 4 times more hp and 5 times more ac than you. So what is the point?</P><P>We need a normal Dot that does about 4k damage in a minute. And Bane dots that do about 6k damage a minute. And lures that do 2k a minute. <BR><hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote></P><P>Dunkel you make a good point there. I hadnt quite thought of this along those lines. I agree with your points, but rather than thinking we need an upgrade to our dots or specialist Bane dots, you have made me think along another line.</P><P>I think your primary point is that with all of our DOTs loaded we generate so much aggro that we will definately be summoned and slaughtered. Possibly the issue here is with Aggro generation and that old hoary chestnut dot stacking.</P><P>If we could stack all of our dots and other necros could stack all of theirs and NOT get summoned, we are then once again damage dealers. To me the aggro generated from a spell as simple as EB is rediculous. Why is it that I can drop an EB on a MOB which is at 15% health, after its been Tash'd, Malo'd, cripple'd, Massively Nuked, backstabbed, beaten on by 30 tanks and then I get summoned?.</P><P>That to me makes absolutely NO sense at all. The aggro generation on our DOTs needs to be seriously re-examined.</P><P>I dont think we can seriously look at ourselves and our damage in comparison to any other class at all. Tanks etc are always going to do more dps than us because their damage is gear dependant and they can stand in front of a mob and smack away without the issues of mana/spell aggro/recast times etc etc.</P><P>However, we are a damage dealing class, we should be able to do a "decent" amount of damage to a MOB. I think we all agree that during a long fight we can do serious damage to a mob, but how many fights in raid encounters last longer than one minute?. What we are looking for I think is an ability to do damage during "short" fights. (IE Kael arena, NToV, rings of fire etc)</P><P>In these cases I think your suggestion of a high damage, short cast, short duration DOT is a good one and I agree that it would not make us overpowered as they are dots to be used in raid situations.</P><P>However I can see several issues arising from out of such an implementation.<BR>1. Aggro. If VI follows the "rules" they seem to have about aggro on our fast casting DOTs (CoC, EB etc) then the aggro generated after the casting of said DOTs would be a guaranteed death sentence. Aggro is something that needs to be examined in the greater scope of caster balancing.<BR>2. Placement of the spells. They will be placed on "uber" encounter MOBs that most of us will never see, therefore the DOTs will not be available to you and I and the whole problem remains static.</P><P>To this end is why I would rather see a short duration, medium damage DOT with low aggro, which could be placed on a vendor. Some thing like this:<BR>Level 55<BR>Vendor purchasable<BR>Expensive, say a 2k cost price.<BR>Venom of the Shissar<BR>Cast time: 5 sec<BR>Duration: 48 sec<BR>Damage: 2400<BR>Very Low aggro, marked to only work on Mobs 50+. Thats a DPS of 50/sec. On long (Uber encounter) fights this could be cast multiple times by the same Nec and would then be doing a reasonable but not ungodly amount of damage. The restriction to 50+ Mobs would mean the average Necro is not going to use this while soloing as not many of us would be hunting MOBs within 5 levels of ourselves at purchase time.</P><P>All I am trying to do is come up with something that VI is likely to swallow. If we suggest a spell with say 45sec duration and 4k damage I doubt we would ever see it. A spell like the above I believe would be more acceptable in terms of "caster Balancing" because we arent treading on the toes of wizzies/shammies etc in terms of DPS.</P><P>Another idea I would like to throw at you Dunkel is the issue of spell availabilty. Now I am going on memory here so bear with me if I get anything blatantly wrong.</P><P>VI has said that a lot of our spells are "bonus" spells, IE the non skelly illusion DD's/the mythical group DMF etc.<BR>They have, I believe, also claimed that a lot of casters resisted the ideas of taking research further and giving us the ability to research our higher level spells. Im not sure who resisted this as a lot of the suggestions posted on this board in the last caster balancing talks were along the lines of being able to research the 55+ spells again.</P><P>VI has also made concerned noises about Mudflation and the amount of PP available to players, particularly on the "elder" servers.</P><P>My idea is this, and I believe it would kill 2 birds with one stone. Basically put the 51+ dropped spells onto Vendors, even 1 particular Vendor in someplace like the bazaar. Make these spells REALLY expensive IE:<BR>51 500pp each<BR>52 750pp each<BR>up to 60 at 10K each for example.</P><P>This would mean that they would be taking PP out of the game, but the spells then become a lot more available to those of us who are unable for one reason or another, to regularly hunt in "uber" zones.</P><P>If it drops for you on a raid, good on you, you have saved yourself 10K. If it doesnt, you still have the ability to actually aquire those spells with some judicious hunting and saving/begging/borrowing etc. When I looked at the thread of Hi level necros still missing major spells at 60 like EOT and Pyre it made me mad.</P><P>And I see the spam in /trade for people selling those spells to desperate necros for 100K+, because noone wants a necro to go on a lot of those raids because we arent needed, because we cant get the spells which make us group friendly, because they are incredibly rare drops, off uber mobs that we dont get to hunt because noone wants us in a raid, we are in a Catch-22 situation.</P><P>Meanwhile the Tanks who have looted these spells take that 100K and go away and buy themselves uber_weapon_99 and uber_armor_99, they have increased their power 10 fold while the (now) poor necro has simply recieved a spell he/she should have in the first place. Like Tanks and weapons, without our spells we are nothing.</P><P>Sorry that devolved into a bit of a rant, but hopefully you have gotten the idea enough to make comments.</P><P>BTW:  <BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>Ulaa, you are one really nice person. Always polite and argumentative.  <hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote><BR>Thank you very much!! *blush*. I dont "try" to be argumentative, I just try to generate some form of reasonable discussion. Theres no point in slagging people off because it just makes everybody mad and nothing useful is achieved (god I sound like Im in HR dont I).<BR>Having said that I am also quite happy to get into a slagging match (and have done in the past) if someone else starts one with me LOL. <img src=icon_smile_big.gif border=0 align=middle></P><P>Also to me a good argument is fun, even one which devolves into the personal, then, the trick becomes to insult the other person as effectively as possible without swearing or name calling.</P><P>Thats why I love this Board. I saw Magister post on the wizzie board during a major flame war they were having.  I dont remember his exact words, but it was something along the lines of "You guys think this is flamage?, come to the Necro boards and we will teach you the meaning of the word!" <img src=icon_smile_wink.gif border=0 align=middle></P><P>56 DE Necromancer<BR><br><BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=49001" target="_blank">Profile</a><BR><a href="http://sizzlesites.com/Ulaa/" target="_blank">Ulaa's web site</a><br><BR><img src="http://www.sizzlesites.com/Ulaa/sig.jpg" border=0></font></td>
