mob is a guaranteed way to grab and HOLD aggro from the MT. In a raid situation the Mob will not attack anyone else until you are dead and by then you have messed up the aggro rota and the whole raid dies. This is a quick way to never get invited to a raid again.</P><P>Ebolt and CoC are nice for soloing except for two major issues on both of them. The first issue is resistances. Both of them are highly resisted. Whats the point of casting a low mana high damage dot if you have to cast it twice to get it to stick. Suddenly the mana ratio looks like crap for that spell. With CoC one resist makes it a 500 mana for 1k damage. I find CoC/Ebolt are resisted 50% of the time at least so I dont use it anymore.</P><P>The second issue is really confined to Ebolt and its the DD component. By 55+ most Necs are almost exclusively root/dotting. The DD component of Ebolt makes this a useless spell because it will break root about 95% of the time, thats if it isnt resisted from the start.</P><P>So our two fastest damage DOTs (which are needed on raids) have Serious disadvantages for both soloing and grouping. I like both these spells and would really like to be able to use them a lot more. But for the above reasons I dont, they sit at the back of my spell book, and every now and again I look at them wistfully and forget them again.</P><P>The other Upgraded spell I would like to see is a 58-60 version of is Splurt. </P><P>This is one of the best spells VI has created for us and every Nec loves it. But at the time you start to get to around 58+ its really at the low end of the damage scale for the MOBs you are hunting.</P><P>Say a spell along the following lines at 58:<BR>350 Mana<BR>4 Sec cast time<BR>2500 damage over 2mins<BR>with the same sort of damage per tick increase ratio as splurt.</P><P>You would have to be VERY careful with stacking that one as with that spell and any other DOT on a mob, in a raid the final couple of ticks would definately get you summoned.</P><P>56 DE Necromancer<BR><br><BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=49001" target="_blank">Profile</a><BR><a href="http://sizzlesites.com/Ulaa/" target="_blank">Ulaa's web site</a><br><BR><img src="http://www.sizzlesites.com/Ulaa/sig.jpg" border=0></font></td>
